com.mousebird.maply

Class SamplingParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mousebird.maply.SamplingParams

  • public class SamplingParams
extends java.lang.Object
    Sampling parameters. These are used to describe how we want to break down the globe or flat projection onto the globe.

      • setMinImportanceTop

        public void setMinImportanceTop(double minImportTop)
        Normally we always load the lowest level, but this can be set to a screen importance as in setMinImportance. In that case we don't load the lowest level unless it exceeds that size.

      • setForceMinLevel

        public void setForceMinLevel(boolean force)
        If set, we'll always make sure the min level is loaded in to provide some background. Turn it off for true single level loading. Not great for basemaps. On by default.

      • setLevelLoads

        public void setLevelLoads(int[] levels)
        Detail the levels you want loaded in target level mode. The layer calculates the optimal target level. The entries in this array are relative to that level or absolute. For example [0,-4,-2] means the layer will always try to load levels 0, targetLevel-4 and targetLevel-2, but only the latter two if they make sense.
